<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178298>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species. Overall dorsal views. A, holotype male (cl 19.5 mm, cw 20.3 mm) (NMCR 19114), Philippines; B, paratype male (cl 19.9 mm, cw 22.0 mm) (ZRC), Philippines; C, male (cl 15.6 mm, cw 16.8 mm) (ZRC), Vanuatu." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178298/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178299>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species. Holotype male (cl 19.5 mm, cw 20.3 mm) (NMCR 19114), Philippines. A, dorsal view of carapace; B, ventral view of carapace; C, buccal area showing third maxillipeds; D, frontal view of carapace and chelipeds." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178299/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178304>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Buccal field, showing mouthparts and mandibles. A, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); B, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003, male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); C, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC); D, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178304/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178305>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Anterior part of thoracic sternum and male abdominal somites 5, 6 and telson. A, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); B, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); C, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); D, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003, male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981: male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Platypilumnus gracilipes Alcock, 1894, male (cl 25.3 mm, cw 29.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.717); G, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC 1997.442); H, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH). Abbreviations: t = telson, a 4 – 6 = male abdominal somites 4 to 6 respectively, st 4 – 7 = sternites 4 to 7 respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178305/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178306>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Posterior part of thoracic sternum and male abdominal somites 3 – 5. A, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); B, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); C, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); D, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003: male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981, male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Platypilumnus gracilipes Alcock, 1894, male (cl 25.3 mm, cw 29.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.717); G, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC 1997.442); H, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH). Abbreviations: t = telson, a 2 – 5 = male abdominal somites 2 to 5 respectively, st 7 = sternites 7, c 5 = coxa of P 5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178306/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178309>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Structure and position of penis, coxa of P 5 and episternite 7 (position of penis indicated by arrow). A, B, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); C, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); D, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981, male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl, 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH). Abbreviations: p = penis, st 7 and 8 = sternites 7 and 8 respectively, es 7 = episternite 7, c 5 = coxa of P 5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178308>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Sterno-abdominal cavity, showing position of press button of abdominal locking mechanism (indicated by arrows) and sternal sutures. A, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); B, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); C, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); D, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003, male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981, male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Platypilumnus gracilipes Alcock, 1894, male (cl 25.3 mm, cw 29.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.717); G, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC 1997.442); H, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH). Abbreviations: pb = press button of abdominal locking mechanism, st 4 – 7 = sternites 4 to 7 respectively, c 5 = coxa of P 5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178308/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178300>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species. Holotype male (cl 19.5 mm, cw 20.3 mm) (NMCR 19114), Philippines. A, outer surface of right chela; B, outer surface of left chela; C, right side of thoracic sternum showing ventral surface of chelipeds and spines on ambulatory meri; D, right P 4." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178307>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Posterior part of carapace showing posterior carapace margin, male abdominal somites 1 and 2, and coxa of last ambulatory legs. A, Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species, paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC); B, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); C, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); D, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003, male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981, male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Platypilumnus gracilipes Alcock, 1894, male (cl 25.3 mm, cw 29.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.717); G, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC 1997.442); H, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH). Abbreviations: t = telson, a 1 – 3 = male abdominal somites 1 to 3 respectively, c 5 = coxa of P 5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178307/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178301>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Vultocinus anfractus, new genus, new species. Paratype male (cl 27.3 mm, cw 25.3 mm) (ZRC), Philippines. A, left third maxilliped (setae denuded); B, male abdomen (partially denuded); C, left G 1, dorsal view; D, left G 1, ventral view; E, distal part of left G 1, dorsal view; F, distal part of left G 1, ventral view; G, left G 2; H, distal part of left G 2. Scales = 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178301/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178303>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Goneplax, new species, male (cl 21.3 mm cw 35.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.700). A, buccal field, showing mouthparts and mandibles; B, anterior part of thoracic sternum and male abdominal somites 5, 6 and telson; C, posterior part of carapace showing posterior carapace margin, male abdominal somites 1 and 2, and coxa of last ambulatory legs; D, posterior part of thoracic sternum and male abdominal somites 3 – 5; E, sterno-abdominal cavity, showing position of press button of abdominal locking mechanism (indicated by arrow) and sternal sutures; F, structure and position of penis, coxa of P 5 and episternite 7. Abbreviations: p = penis, pb = press button of abdominal locking mechanism, t = telson, a 1 - 6 = male abdominal somites 1 to 6 respectively, st 4 - 8 = sternites 4 to 8 respectively, es 7 = episternite 7, c 5 = coxa of P 5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178303/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.178302>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Overall views. A, Goneplax, new species: male (cl 21.3 mm cw 35.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.700); B, “ Goneplax ” marivenae Komatsu & Takeda, 2004, male (cl 11.0 mm, cw 17.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.724); C, Carcinoplax spinosissima Rathbun, 1914, male (cl 24.0 mm, cw 29.1 mm) (ZRC 2001.535); D, Mathildella rubra Ng & Ho, 2003, male (cl 16.2 mm, cw 19.5 mm) (ZRC 2004.535); E, Intesius pilosus Guinot & Richer de Forges, 1981, male (cl 32.3 mm, cw 38.3 mm) (ZRC 2004.731); F, Platypilumnus gracilipes Alcock, 1894, male (cl 25.3 mm, cw 29.6 mm) (ZRC 2004.717); G, Progeryon mus Ng & Guinot, 1999, holotype male (cl 38.6 mm, cw 46.5 mm) (ZRC 1997.442); H, Conleyus defodio Ng & Ng, 2003, holotype male (cl, 12.2 mm, cw 16.4 mm) (FLMNH)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/178302/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

